==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sora
<hw>So"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
North American rail (<spn>Porzana Carolina</spn>) common in the Eastern
United States. Its back is golden brown, varied with black and white,
the front of the head and throat black, the breast and sides of the head
and neck slate-colored. Called also <altname>American rail</altname>,
<altname>Carolina rail</altname>, <altname>Carolina crake</altname>,
<altname>common rail</altname>, <altname>sora rail</altname>,
<altname>soree</altname>, <altname>meadow chicken</altname>, and
<altname>orto</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>King sora</b></col>, <cd>the Florida
gallinule.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sorance</ent>⟦br⟧
